<main>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">shorts-ready linux demos</p>
    <h1>Tiny commands. Real failures. Safer fixes.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Linux One Liners is a command rescue library built from reproducible terminal demos. Each lesson can become a web page, YouTube Short, LinkedIn post, transcript, and later a voiceover video.</p>
    <div class="status-panel">
      <p class="label">Now building</p>
      <p><%= site["build_status"]["now_building"] %></p>
      <p class="small-note">First-party analytics are active so traffic, load, and buyer diligence can be measured from day one.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button" href="#lessons">Browse lessons</a>
      <a class="button ghost" href="#workflow">See the pipeline</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="lessons" class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">first batch</p>
      <h2>Command rescue cards</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="lesson-grid">
      <% lessons.each do |lesson| %>
        <article class="lesson-card">
          <div class="card-meta">
            <span><%= series_title(lesson["series"]) %></span>
            <span class="danger <%= lesson["danger"] %>"><%= lesson["danger"] %></span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="lessons/<%= lesson["slug"] %>/"><%= lesson["title"] %></a></h3>
          <p><%= lesson["hook"] %></p>
          <code><%= lesson["command"] %></code>
        </article>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="series" class="section split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">curriculum engine</p>
      <h2>Series, not random clips</h2>
      <p>Shorts are the atomic unit, but the site organizes them into playlists, pages, and future paid packs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="series-list">
      <% series.each do |item| %>
        <article>
          <h3><%= item["title"] %></h3>
          <p><%= item["summary"] %></p>
        </article>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="workflow" class="section workflow">
    <p class="eyebrow">production model</p>
    <h2>One source, many outputs</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Write a structured lesson with problem, command, danger level, demo steps, and recovery notes.</li>
      <li>Run it inside a disposable container or VM fixture.</li>
      <li>Capture terminal frames, captions, transcript, and short-form metadata.</li>
      <li>Publish the web page, YouTube Short, LinkedIn post, and later a course unit.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">curation gate</p>
      <h2>Every lesson has to earn its slot</h2>
      <p>New content is checked for safety notes, reproducible demo steps, Shorts metadata, a LinkedIn question, and an experiment metric before it ships.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="series-list">
      <article>
        <h3>Required</h3>
        <p>Problem, command, danger rating, when not to use it, undo or recovery, expected output, and demo commands.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Distribution</h3>
        <p>Shorts title, voiceover seed, caption, YouTube playlist, LinkedIn question, and CTA.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Business signal</h3>
        <p>Each lesson gets an A/B test metric so we can learn what attracts traffic, saves, clicks, and eventual revenue.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="exports" class="section split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">distribution</p>
      <h2>Platform copy is generated too</h2>
      <p>Each lesson carries Shorts, YouTube, and LinkedIn metadata so traffic loops can be produced from one source file.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="series-list">
      <article>
        <h3><a data-track="export_click" data-track-label="shorts_json" href="exports/shorts.json">Shorts metadata</a></h3>
        <p>Titles, captions, target duration, playlist, and voiceover seed text.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3><a data-track="export_click" data-track-label="linkedin_posts" href="exports/linkedin-posts.md">LinkedIn post seeds</a></h3>
        <p>Hooks, command snippets, questions, and calls to action for engagement testing.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3><a data-track="export_click" data-track-label="analytics_events" href="exports/analytics-events.json">Analytics event contract</a></h3>
        <p>Privacy-light events to measure copy clicks, export clicks, lesson depth, and outbound video intent.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">profit path</p>
      <h2>Build, measure, monetize, package</h2>
      <p>The goal is not decoration. Each deploy should make the site easier to grow, measure, monetize, or sell.</p>
    </div>
    <ol class="queue-list">
      <% site["build_status"]["next_up"].each do |item| %>
        <li><%= item %></li>
      <% end %>
    </ol>
  </section>
</main>
